From: scheme <scheme@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] mlx4_en: do not request physical flow control from a VF

The PF owns physical Ethernet flow-control state.  When mlx4_en loads in a
guest VF with its normal default profile, it requests global RX/TX pause.
The PF correctly rejects that operation while retaining the configured
RoCE PFC policy, leaving unnecessary host diagnostics on every VF reload.

For a slave/VF, request neither global pause nor physical PFC from
mlx4_en.  VLAN PCP and physical PFC remain configured on the PF.
Preserve existing behavior for the PF and for non-multifunction devices.

This guest patch requires the host PF to configure the intended RoCE PFC
policy.
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/en_main.c | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/en_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/en_main.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/en_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/en_main.c
@@ -163,10 +163,10 @@ static void mlx4_en_get_profile(struct mlx4_en_dev *mdev)
 		params->udp_rss = 0;
 	}
 	for (i = 1; i <= MLX4_MAX_PORTS; i++) {
-		params->prof[i].rx_pause = !(pfcrx || pfctx);
-		params->prof[i].rx_ppp = pfcrx;
-		params->prof[i].tx_pause = !(pfcrx || pfctx);
-		params->prof[i].tx_ppp = pfctx;
+		params->prof[i].rx_pause = !mlx4_is_slave(mdev->dev) && !(pfcrx || pfctx);
+		params->prof[i].rx_ppp = mlx4_is_slave(mdev->dev) ? 0 : pfcrx;
+		params->prof[i].tx_pause = !mlx4_is_slave(mdev->dev) && !(pfcrx || pfctx);
+		params->prof[i].tx_ppp = mlx4_is_slave(mdev->dev) ? 0 : pfctx;
 		if (mlx4_low_memory_profile()) {
 			params->prof[i].tx_ring_size = MLX4_EN_MIN_TX_SIZE;
 			params->prof[i].rx_ring_size = MLX4_EN_MIN_RX_SIZE;
-- 
